I am not familiar with ksp mod programming and I apparently played hooky for all my classes in - omnipotence 101 (smile).

UPDATE:

So I pulled the IFS mod from the extension and replaced it with the updated .15 version and now the game will not load. It hangs in the late modulemanager process. This is why mods that include other mods that I might already have installed kind of makes me nuts. I had to then delete the MM cache and try to load again which also failed.

Fortunately, I have bounced off this wall before and I always make a copy of my current running game before updating anything so I was able to roll back to the version of kspi-e before I installed the mk2 expanision and this mod.

However, I would like to know if there is a proper installation order so that I can try to install it again.

Also, some suggestions and critiques:

The electrical generator parts are very long compared to the 1.25m ones from KSPI Extended. If they were half as long as they are, that would work much better. This can be done by messing with the various scale factors in the MODEL{} section of that part's config.

There is no Antimatter reactor. There's an Antimatter-initiated-fusion reactor, but that's not the same. Antimatter reactors put out MUCH more power than any of the existing Mk2 reactor types. Example: the 1.25m antimatter reactor puts out 5GW standard, 15GW upgraded.

There is no Mk2 antimatter storage tank.

There are no intake pre-coolers in Mk2 form-factor. This makes the Mk2 Expansion intakes not very useful for spaceplanes, because there's no easy way to squeeze a pre-cooler in there without making it look like it was strapped-on as an afterthought.

Parts that have a pre-cooler module shouldn't be able to hold resources. The pre-cooler machinery takes up any space where propellant could have gone.

Not all wings have radiator modules in them, and the radiator modules that are there, don't have enough power dissipation to cope with any of the reactors included.

Some of the parts that have resource switching in them, aren't able to switch between all the KSPI resources, just between LF/LFO/Structural (Mk2 bi-coupler, others).
